com.ihealth.communication.control

Interface HsProfile


  • public interface HsProfile
    Public APIs for the Hs serials device profiles

    Clients need to call iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(com.ihealth.communication.manager.iHealthDevicesCallback) register. When new data from Hs device, The Callback {#iHealthDevicesCallback #onDeviceNotify} can be triggered should call.

        Constant Field Values

      • ERROR_NUM_HS

        static final java.lang.String ERROR_NUM_HS
        The key of error ID number of HS device.

        Flag Error number of Bp device.

          Error code and Description

          1:Battery level is low.

          2:The Scale failed to initialize.

          3:Maximum weight has been exceeded.

          4:The Scale can't capture a steady reading.

          5:Bluetooth connection error.

          6:Movement while measuring.

          7:Invalidate.

          8:Scale memory access error.

          9:No memory.

          10:Device disconnect.

          11:Communication error.

          12:HS4DeviceRecWeightError.

          13:Failed to create measurement connections.

          14:Instruction timeout.

          600:the argument of method is illegal.

          700:the operation is illegal.

          400:ERROR_ID_ILLEGAL_ARGUMENT indicates parameter error.

          500:ERROR_ID_WIFI_DISABLED indicates wifi is disabled.

        See Also:

  • USERINFO_IN_HS

    static final java.lang.String USERINFO_IN_HS
    The key of whether user information in the scale or not.
    • 1 indicates that user is in scale
    • 2 indicates that user isn't in scale and the sale has free position
    • 3 indicates that user isn't in scale but the sale is full need delete other user with method DeleteUserInScale(int)
